WEBVTT

00:17.408 --> 00:20.107
The Italians, they want
to keep me in shackles.

00:20.237 --> 00:22.196
To them,
Harlem is a cotton field,

00:22.326 --> 00:23.632
and I'm the house nigger.

00:23.762 --> 00:25.242
How you doin'? Joe Colombo.

00:25.373 --> 00:26.809
Hey.

00:26.939 --> 00:28.811
Make up your debt to
the Families by working with me.

00:28.941 --> 00:31.292
Otherwise... the Families
will need to be paid

00:31.422 --> 00:32.771
in full by Friday.

00:32.902 --> 00:34.338
Omar.

00:34.469 --> 00:36.340
You betrayed me,

00:36.471 --> 00:38.212
you betrayed this woman,

00:38.342 --> 00:40.040
and you betrayed Islam.

00:40.170 --> 00:41.998
I lost the woman I love,

00:42.129 --> 00:44.087
the mosque I loved,

00:44.218 --> 00:45.828
and the brother
I grew up with in this faith.

00:45.958 --> 00:49.397
I just want your forgiveness
before I die.

00:49.527 --> 00:52.791
As much as I want to, I can't
spill a Black man's blood.

00:52.922 --> 00:56.143
Let Allah decide his fate.

00:56.273 --> 00:57.100
<i>With Chin up in Lewisburg,</i>

00:57.231 --> 00:58.536
<i>everything has gone to shit.</i>

00:58.667 --> 01:01.409
<i>They fuckin' got him
poppin' his own assoc--</i>

01:01.539 --> 01:03.367
You have helped throw
the Five Families

01:03.498 --> 01:04.629
into total disarray.

01:04.760 --> 01:06.283
I hope they all
kill each other.

01:06.414 --> 01:07.589
She'll fucking rat.

01:07.719 --> 01:10.070
She put her
own father away, Tommy.

01:10.200 --> 01:12.246
This is your husband
Chin's fucking problem.

01:12.376 --> 01:14.074
Why isn't he
taking care of it?

01:14.204 --> 01:16.467
You don't think that he knows
she should go?

01:18.600 --> 01:21.255
Aaah!

01:21.385 --> 01:23.300
The Reverend
was just telling me

01:23.431 --> 01:25.259
that he got government funding
for Harlem.

01:25.389 --> 01:27.261
The Negro bank
is going to receive

01:27.391 --> 01:30.481
a huge influx of cash.

01:30.612 --> 01:31.221
That's great.

01:31.352 --> 01:33.354
Hands up!

01:34.877 --> 01:37.097
Here's the money.

01:37.227 --> 01:38.707
Harlem? It's mine.

01:43.451 --> 01:47.237
We don't feel
that in 1964

01:47.368 --> 01:48.369
that we should have
to sit around and wait

01:48.499 --> 01:50.762
for some degree of civil rights.

01:50.893 --> 01:52.286
No. We want it now,

01:52.416 --> 01:54.723
or we don't think
anybody should have it.

02:05.647 --> 02:07.605
- How goes it, Kev?
- It's all good.

02:07.736 --> 02:08.737
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

02:08.867 --> 02:09.825
Alright.

02:09.955 --> 02:13.263
How my men been behaving?

02:13.394 --> 02:15.135
Well, they scared
the mailman a few times.

02:17.224 --> 02:18.921
The neighbors were upset.

02:19.051 --> 02:20.792
Until they realized
they now live

02:20.923 --> 02:22.664
on the safest block in Queens.

02:24.709 --> 02:26.407
Good, good.

02:26.537 --> 02:30.411
Yeah, my neighbors
are almost as grateful as I am.

02:32.674 --> 02:34.284
You know I won't be able
to protect you

02:34.415 --> 02:35.807
if you go on this foolish trip
to Africa, right?

02:35.938 --> 02:37.809
The only reason I'm going
is because I know

02:37.940 --> 02:40.682
your men will be here
to protect my family.

02:40.812 --> 02:43.728
They will. You got my word.

02:43.859 --> 02:46.122
And I'm going to want
to take Elise with me,

02:46.253 --> 02:47.471
as my secretary.

02:47.602 --> 02:49.473
She can join me
after my trip to Mecca.

02:49.604 --> 02:51.432
Elise?

02:51.562 --> 02:52.824
Can't allow that.

02:52.955 --> 02:54.478
She needs to be here,
look after Margaret.

02:54.609 --> 02:57.786
I'm sure Mayme can handle things
for a week or two.

02:57.916 --> 03:01.355
This is
an incredible opportunity.

03:01.485 --> 03:04.575
She has so much potential, Bumpy.

03:04.706 --> 03:06.577
In many ways,
she's just like you.

03:06.708 --> 03:08.797
That a compliment?

03:11.669 --> 03:16.196
My friend, the decision
should be hers, don't you think?

03:18.676 --> 03:21.331
The reason for this trip
is not foolish.

03:21.462 --> 03:24.334
It's to seek alliances
with the African Leaders.

03:24.465 --> 03:26.206
I need their help if we are
going to win our fight

03:26.336 --> 03:27.729
for freedom here at home.

03:27.859 --> 03:30.427
It's a good idea.

03:30.558 --> 03:31.863
Maybe they can lend me
a couple of men

03:31.994 --> 03:33.517
to fight off the Italians.
What do you think?

03:35.824 --> 03:39.001
Ah, I've come to realize
that you and I believe

03:39.131 --> 03:42.222
we can solve
all our problems by ourselves.

03:44.876 --> 03:45.834
We can't.

03:55.539 --> 03:57.541
Thanks for everything,
Mrs. Allen. See you Sunday.

04:05.767 --> 04:07.986
Excuse me. Mrs. Johnson.

04:08.117 --> 04:11.338
My boss would be honored with
just a few minutes of your time.

04:11.468 --> 04:14.384
And who are you?
Who's your boss?

04:14.515 --> 04:16.908
Don't worry. I assure you
you are in no danger.

04:17.039 --> 04:19.694
Leg of lamb doesn't keep well
in the heat.

04:19.824 --> 04:22.392
- I should really be going.
- We could give you a lift.

04:22.523 --> 04:24.960
You live right over
in Lenox Terrace, right?

04:25.090 --> 04:26.875
It's no trouble at all.

04:33.925 --> 04:35.579
Mrs. Johnson.

04:35.710 --> 04:39.279
I'm Joe Colombo. It's my
pleasure to meet you. Come on.

04:54.076 --> 04:56.687
<i>♪ Yeah</i>

04:56.818 --> 04:59.429
<i>♪ Change</i>

04:59.560 --> 05:02.693
<i>♪ Yeah</i>

